<p><strong>Golem Greatbow</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatbows" href="/Greatbows" target="">Greatbow</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Golem Greatbow</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for ranged combat.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Greatbow of black stone crafted by a civilization now gone to<br>ruin. Weapon of the Guardian Golem.<br><br>Extremely heavy, this greatbow requires enormous strength just to<br>draw, suggesting it was not designed for human use.<br></em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Golem Greatbow in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Golem Greatbow&nbsp;has a chance to drop from any <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Golem" href="/Golem" target="">Golem</a> archer.&nbsp;The Golem Greatbow does not drop from Golems with halberds.</p> 
<p>Locations of respawning Golem archers:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>One can be found on the Limgrave Tower Bridge in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stormhill" href="/Stormhill" target="">Stormhill</a>, which can be accessed from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stormveil Castle" href="/Stormveil+Castle">Stormveil Castle</a>.&nbsp;Two halberd Golems are also found on the bridge.</li> 
 <li>Two can be found on the path towards the colosseum in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Caelid" href="/Caelid">Caelid</a>. This location is only accessible&nbsp;via a lift in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Siofra River" href="/Siofra+River">Siofra River</a>&nbsp;that takes the player to the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Deep Siofra Well" href="/Deep+Siofra+Well">Deep Siofra Well</a>. 
  <ul> 
   <li>These two Golem archers fire magic-imbued explosive arrows and are also the only source of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Golem's Magic Arrow" href="/Golem's+Magic+Arrow" target="">Golem's Magic Arrow</a>.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>One can be found next to the top of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Grand Lift of Dectus" href="/Grand+Lift+of+Dectus" target="">Grand Lift of Dectus</a>, in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Altus Plateau" href="/Altus+Plateau" target="">Altus Plateau</a>. It is accompanied by a single halberd Golem. 
  <ul> 
   <li>If the Grand Lift of Dectus is activated&nbsp;after finding both halves of the Dectus Medallion, the Golems guarding the lift will be non-hostile until the the player initiates combat. (needs confirmation,&nbsp;not sure if the game checks for possession&nbsp;of the medallion or usage of the lift)</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>Locations of non-respawning Golem archers:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>One&nbsp;can be found outside the entrance of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Castle Morne" href="/Castle+Morne" target="">Castle Morne</a>, at the southern tip of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weeping Peninsula" href="/Weeping+Peninsula">Weeping Peninsula</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2918&amp;lat=-224.23&amp;lng=111.68&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2918&amp;lat=-224.23&amp;lng=111.68&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
 <li>Two can be&nbsp;found in the north-eastern&nbsp;section of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Capital Outskirts" href="/Capital+Outskirts">Capital Outskirts</a>, on the&nbsp;hill approaching the northern entrance to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Leyndell Royal Capital (Legacy Dungeon)" href="/Leyndell+Royal+Capital+(Legacy+Dungeon)" target="">Leyndell Royal Capital (Legacy Dungeon)</a>.</li> 
 <li>One can be found in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mountaintops of the Giants" href="/Mountaintops+of+the+Giants" target="">Mountaintops of the Giants</a>, guarding the tall and narrow path north.&nbsp;</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Golem Greatbow Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Through and Through" href="/Through+and+Through" target="">Through and Through</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Golem Greatbow</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Farming tips: 
  <ul> 
   <li>When a Golem falls over, the player can perform a&nbsp;Critical Attack by attacking it's chest.</li> 
   <li>The best places to farm Golem archers for this greatbow are: 
    <ul> 
     <li>The pair of Golem archers in Caelid that are located on the path towards the colosseum. The player can fast travel to the Deep Siofra Well Site of Grace to respawn the archers. Note that the archer closer to the colosseum does not have weakspots in it's feet.</li> 
     <li>The Golem archer next to the Grand Lift of Dectus. The Altus Plateau Site of Grace is nearby, north of the lift.</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
   <li>The Limgrave Tower Bridge is an early game option, as the Golems here have less health than in other encounters. However, the player is unable to summon their mount at this location and the Golem archer&nbsp;spawns&nbsp;at the broken&nbsp;part of the bridge, near the Waygate to the the Divine Tower of Limgrave. Two halberd-wielding Golems also spawn along the way which can interfere with farming.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
 <li>Base drop rate is 10% (at 100 Discovery).</li> 
 <li>You can shoot greatbows fairly quickly if you jump and start firing midair. Your character will land with the bow already drawn and fire the arrow in a moment. Obviously much slower than long or short bows but still fast enough to use against bosses if you keep your distance.</li> 
 <li>All Bows (not <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Crossbows" href="/Crossbows" target="">Crossbows</a>) only need 2/3 the STR requirement, since they can only be used two-handed.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Golem Greatbow</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Golem Greatbow Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Golem Greatbow Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a> nor boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
