				<li id="16643769" class="cmnt-root" data="12" data-d="1650609919000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578990/Golem-Greatbow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">22 Apr 2022 02:45</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16643769" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Messing around with a +8 version in the rebirth menu, and physik flasks with testing on some enemies, going from 18 STR and 18 DEX to:<br/> - 45 STR: about ~100 damage increase from ~580 to ~680<br/> - 45 DEX: about ~30 damage increase from ~580 to ~610<br/> - 45 STR and 45 DEX: about ~120 damage increase from ~580 to ~700<br/><br/>The alleged C and D scalings kind of underrate the difference between STR and DEX for this greatbow, with STR being about 3 times as more beneficial per point under the soft cap. The scaling feels more like B in strength and E in DEX at +8 in my opinion. The weight of this thing is huge and you will suffer for it without a bit of an endurance investment, so on anything other than a pure glass cannon setup or &gt;100RL build I&apos;d skip DEX entirely as it&apos;s too little benefit for this weapon considering the investment. Get some vigor and endurance instead and you&apos;ll have a much more pleasant experience using this.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16643769" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" ro