				<li id="16613600" class="cmnt-root" data="95" data-d="1649755659000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578990/Golem-Greatbow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">12 Apr 2022 05:27</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16613600" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">For all of you looking to make a Bow build using Greatbows and don&apos;t know which Bow to take the Golem Greatbow or Lion Greatbow, worry not, I got your back!<br/><br/>I started doing a Bow build a little while ago and therefore looked into these badboys a little deeper. <br/>For those of you who just quickly wanna know which Bow is generally better, I would advice you pick the Golem Greatbow. Further down is the explanation and comparison between Golem and Lion Bow.<br/><br/><br/>1. The Lion Greatbow. <br/>The Lion Bow seems to have a little more Dex scaling than the Golem Bow but it is not that noticeable. Especially since Greatbows generally work best going for a Quality build (Expect Erdtree Greatbow).<br/>However, the Lion Greatbow can still work decently well when used on a Dex Build with only minimal Str investments, thx to its massive damage boost of 20% when using Radahns spears! <br/>The Weapon Art is a super strong against big enemies but lacks damage against smaller and/or faster ones, since it will most likely miss a lot of its arrows. Big boys however, usually eat those raining arrows like candy and therefore tend to melt. <br/>Another good point for this Bow in general is, that it is upgradable with Somber Smithing Stones, making relatively high AR values come in rather quickly. <br/>The biggest weakness of the Lion Greatbow is also its biggest strength, Radahns Spear! The damage increase is absoloutely noticeable as mentioned above, but 1 arrow costs 800 runes!!! Thats more than double the amount of the already expensive normal Great Arrows, while only giving 1/5 more damage and ONLY when used with the Lion Greatbow.<br/>The Lion Greatbow AR when upgraded to +6 with, 50 Str/50 Dex, on a D/D scaling with no Arrows equipped is 365 and 527 when equipped with normal Greatarrows.<br/><br/>Pros:<br/>- Works well for Quality and for Dex.<br/>- Great WA, especially for big and slow bosses. Dragons hate this trick!<br/>- CAN achieve the highest hitting single arrow damage when using Radahns Spears but most likely only for lower rune Levels (below 100).<br/>- Is the lightest of all Greatbows with only 9.5 units.<br/>- Looks freaking dope! <br/><br/>Cons:<br/>- Gets outdamaged by the Golem Greatbow once a certain upgrade and Strength level is achieved.<br/>- Loses a lot of damage potential when not using Radahns Spears.<br/>- WA is rather useless against enemies that are not huge or enemies that move.<br/>- Lower base AR when compared with the Golem Greatbow<br/>- Radahns Spears cost 800 Runes per Arrow. (Actually hilariously expensive.)<br/>- WA can&apos;t be changed.<br/><br/><br/>2. The Golem Greatbow.<br/>The Golem Greatbow works very well on Strength builds, but just like the Lion Greatbow, definetly shines the most when going for Quality.<br/>The Golems WA is Through and Through which massively increases the damage when shoting, albeit for a little bit of FP usage. When positioned well, this WA can kill or massively damage 2 or 3 enemies using one single Arrow! I already happened to see some really funny ingame moments when using this WA and the sneaking around to get the best possible snipe is surprisingly fun.<br/>Just like the Lion Greatbow it is upgraded with Somber Smithing Stones, which means high ARs early on. There are special Arrows for this bow aswell, but they only net a flat 10 AR more than usual Greatarrows and their special AR and &quot;effect&quot; are applied to every Greatbow when used. The Golem Greatarrows seem to have 40% increased poise damage but since Greatbows generally knock everything thats no super elite mob or boss from their feet, this doesn&apos;t really seem to do much. Also these are not buyable, sadly.<br/>The Golem Greatbow AR when upgraded to +6 with, 50 Str/50 Dex, on a C/D scaling with no Arrows equipped is 430 and 607 when equipped with normal Greatarrows.<br/><br/>Pros:<br/>- Amazing on Quality builds and works well for Str.<br/>- WA is really strong and effective against every type of enemy.<br/>- CAN take 1/4 of bosses HP with one arrow.<br/>- Outdamages all other Greatbows on a Quality build.<br/>- Doesn&apos;t need special ammunition.<br/>- Has a &quot;mighty&quot; feeling in its shots.<br/>- Has the highes base AR of all Greatbows<br/><br/>Cons:<br/>- Can&apos;t change its WA<br/>- Needs Str investments and a few upgrades for damage to noticeably kick in.<br/>- The heaviest of all Greatbows with 14.5 units!<br/>- Kinda Ugly, not gonna lie.<br/><br/><br/>Conclusion:<br/>The Golem Greatbow definetly takes the cake when we are talking about damage per arrow. The only way the Lion Greatbow can achieve comparable damage numbers, is when using its special arrows. As soon as Through and Through is getting used, the Golem Greatbow will once again deal significantly more damage. However, the overall dps of the Lion Greatbow can be higher depending on the enemy and the given situation. For general usage the Golem Greatbow is definetly the better choice. The only real downside of it is, that it is very heavy.<br/><br/>When you are looking for a decent Greatbow suitable even for Dex Builds and lower equipment loads or you just wanna go for some Elden Bling, the Lion Greatbow is for you, but you have to consider the special arrow price.<br/><br/>When you are looking for the highest possible sniping damage and you wanna see some 1k+ damage numbers pop up for a single arrow, the Golem Greatbow is your choice.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16613600" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16613600" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">5</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>96</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16613600"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16613600" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16613600"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
