				<li id="16521544" class="cmnt-root" data="4" data-d="1647428964000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=132887" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">Eimaj44</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578990/Golem-Greatbow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">16 Mar 2022 07:09</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16521544" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Just a small addition to this wiki page. I was just testing and you can farm the Archer and Halberd Golem right after you ascend The Grand Lift of Dectus. The way I discovered this was that I was unsure if these were meant to respawn, however I used  the site of grace before the lift cutscene, and died the first time this discovering they are farmable. These golems respawn, thus making it a semi-easy Golem Greatbow and souls farm. So for a really quick and easy farm of the Greatbow if you are in the area and do not have it yet. Go directly left of the lift and rest at the grace on the hill, then just kill them over and over till you get whatever you need.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16521544" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16521544" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</